abstract: With foreign policy emerging as a top priority in the Democratic primary, Pete Buttigieg, a former naval intelligence officer, is leaning harder on his veteran status.
snippet: With foreign policy emerging as a top priority in the Democratic primary, Pete Buttigieg, a former naval intelligence officer, is leaning harder on his veteran status.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CONWAY, N.H. — When Pete Buttigieg, the former mayor of South Bend, Ind., took the stage to deliver his first in-person reaction to the American killing of Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani of Iran, he began with a laundry list of unanswered questions about the airstrike.

abstract: Did you take a step back from politics over the holidays? We’re here to catch you up on the most important moments of the 2020 presidential race last week.
snippet: Did you take a step back from politics over the holidays? We’re here to catch you up on the most important moments of the 2020 presidential race last week.
lead_paragraph: Welcome to 2020. The holidays are over and the barren wasteland of winter stretches ahead of us. But on the bright side, the Iowa caucuses are just 30 days away!

abstract: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
snippet: There hasn’t been a single poll in weeks that could help the Democratic presidential candidates qualify for the next debate. The party blames the polling organizations.
lead_paragraph: NORTH CONWAY, N.H. — The morning after the Democrats’ last debate in December, the Democratic National Committee announced the thresholds to qualify for the next one, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines: 5 percent support in four qualifying polls, or 7 percent in two early-state polls. With those steeper requirements in place, just five candidates have qualified so far: Joe Biden, Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar.

headline_main: D.N.C. Tells Pollsters to Do More Polls

abstract: Foreign affairs have played a strictly limited role so far in the Democratic primary, but the killing of Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani could reshape the contest.
snippet: Foreign affairs have played a strictly limited role so far in the Democratic primary, but the killing of Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani could reshape the contest.
lead_paragraph: The American strike in Baghdad that killed the Iranian general Qassim Suleimani thrust foreign policy to the center of the Democratic presidential race, drawing expressions of grave concern from the leading candidates and stoking a new debate in the party about the American military presence in the Middle East.

abstract: Are the wealthy a liability in 2020? Or will they help get him elected?
snippet: Are the wealthy a liability in 2020? Or will they help get him elected?
lead_paragraph: At an annual charity fund-raiser in October, Anna Wintour, the editor of Vogue, shared a table with the designer Michael Kors and Pete Buttigieg, then the mayor of South Bend, Ind., who wore one of his trademark navy suits.

headline_main: Pete Buttigieg and the One Percent

abstract: The quickest way to get a President Stacey Abrams or President Pete Buttigieg is to first elect a President Biden.
snippet: The quickest way to get a President Stacey Abrams or President Pete Buttigieg is to first elect a President Biden.
lead_paragraph: You may have heard an old crank in a big house ranting about appliances and unflushable toilets the other day. “Remember the dishwasher, you’d press it, boom — there’d be like an explosion,” he said, apropos of nothing. “Now you press it 12 times.”
